9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 224, L.D. 324, “An Act to Increase
10 Reading Proficiency in Public Schools”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Increase Reading and Mathematics Proficiency in Public Schools'
13 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
14 'Sec. 1. Foundation partnership. Resolved: That, in fiscal years 2025-26 and
15 2026-27, the Department of Education may work with a national foundation in order to
16 maximize private resources for reading and mathematics grant programs for school
17 administrative units in the State.
18 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. Resolved: That the following
19 appropriations and allocations are made.
20 EDUCATION, DEPARTMENT OF
21 Innovative Teaching and Learning Z394
22 Initiative: Provides one-time funds in fiscal year 2025-26 and fiscal year 2026-27 only to
23 continue an early literacy grant program as well as for grant programming related to the
24 implementation of best practices for mathematics instruction in schools.
